01/04/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkey's anti-terror envoy, retired army general Edip Baser, wrapped up a several-day visit to the United States on Saturday (March 31st). The focus was on joint activities for combating Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) terrorists. In a statement to the media, Baser said he was confident the US side is sincere in guaranteeing co-operation and joint action in the fight against the PKK. At the same time, he said Ankara had information that certain Iraqi players were supporting the PKK, and again held out the possibility that the Turkish Army could mount a cross-border operation. (Anadolu Agency, Focus - 01/04/07; Anadolu Agency, Zaman - 31/03/07)
